{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3f9f4046-270e-435d-9913-9bc981a0d435","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v2)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v3)** — same as v2, but also adds:\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason\")]           // still works\n[Fact(Explicit = true)]           // runs only when explicitly selected\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll frameworks require (or strongly encourage) a reason string. In MSTest and NUnit the attribute is `[Ignore]`, in TUnit it's `[Skip]`, and in xUnit the skip reason is a named parameter on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c64a9fde-39ce-4ae8-af80-6ff8425a48bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct skip/ignore attributes for MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit test frameworks. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":297,"requestId":"7C14:1E67:9DCF4:C0A9A:69F943A2"},"id":"9fb9963c-08ba-4160-9555-90af90c73b4f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:11:06.264Z","parentId":"6851cc32-cd06-4b3a-a4a2-24c474b88b67"}
